---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About Michelle" description="Meet Michelle — CMI-certified Spanish medical interpreter in Walnut Creek, CA with 13+ years at UCSF Health, Kaiser Permanente, and John Muir Health. Behavioral health specialist. Founder of Mi Voz Interpreting.">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-deep-forest py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20"
         style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 60%, #C4956A 0%, transparent 55%);">
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs tracking-[4px] uppercase text-clay mb-4 font-body">The Person Behind Mi Voz</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl text-cream mb-6 leading-tight">
          Meet <span class="italic text-clay">Michelle.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-mist/80 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">
          Certified Medical Interpreter. Behavioral health specialist. The voice for patients who need one most.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6">
          {[['13+', 'Years of experience'], ['CMI', 'Certified Medical Interpreter'], ['100%', 'HIPAA compliant']].map(([stat, label]) => (
            <div>
              <p class="font-display text-3xl text-clay leading-none">{stat}</p>
              <p class="text-xs tracking-[2px] uppercase text-sage mt-1">{label}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <img src="/images/michelle-headshot-square.jpg"
           alt="Michelle, CMI — founder of Mi Voz Interpreting"
           class="rounded-2xl aspect-square object-cover max-w-sm mx-auto md:mx-0 w-full" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STORY -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-xs tracking-[4px] uppercase text-earth mb-6 font-body">Her Story</p>

    <div class="prose-like space-y-6">
      <p class="text-lg text-bark leading-relaxed">
        Michelle has spent her career doing one thing: making sure Spanish-speaking patients
        are fully heard, understood, and able to advocate for themselves in a healthcare system
        that wasn't built with them in mind.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-clay pl-6 my-10">
        <p class="font-display italic text-2xl text-forest leading-relaxed">
          "Mi Voz means My Voice. It's the voice I lend to patients who walk into a clinic
          afraid, confused, and unable to communicate what they're feeling — until I'm there."
        </p>
        <footer class="mt-4 text-sm text-earth">— Michelle, Founder</footer>
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-bark/80 leading-relaxed">
        With over 13 years of professional experience, Michelle is a Certified Medical Interpreter
        based in Walnut Creek, CA. She has worked with major health systems including UCSF Health,
        John Muir Health, and Kaiser Permanente, as well as community-focused nonprofits like
        RotaCare Bay Area. She serves the Diablo Valley in person and patients and providers
        anywhere in the US by video or phone.
      </p>

      <p class="text-bark/80 leading-relaxed">
        What drives her isn't the business — it's the moment a patient's face relaxes because
        they finally understand what's happening to their own body. It's the doctor who can
        finally have a real conversation with their patient. It's the family that walks out of
        a consultation feeling informed, not lost.
      </p>

      <p class="text-bark/80 leading-relaxed">
        That's why Mi Voz exists. And that's what Michelle brings to every appointment —
        whether it's on-site, over video, or by phone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CREDENTIALS -->
  <section class="bg-cream py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="text-xs tracking-[4px] uppercase text-earth mb-4 font-body">Credentials & Training</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-deep-forest mb-12">
        The expertise you can <span class="italic">count on.</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { icon: '🎓', title: 'Certified Medical Interpreter', desc: 'Nationally certified with formal training in healthcare interpreting standards, ethics, and medical terminology.' },
          { icon: '🏛️', title: 'Agency Experience', desc: 'Trained and worked at Language World, a leading California language services agency.' },
          { icon: '🔒', title: 'HIPAA Certified', desc: 'Full HIPAA compliance training and commitment to patient privacy in every engagement.' },
          { icon: '🩺', title: 'Medical Terminology', desc: 'Deep fluency in Spanish and English medical terminology across specialties.' },
          { icon: '⚖️', title: 'Code of Ethics', desc: 'Commitment to accuracy, confidentiality, impartiality, and professional boundaries.' },
          { icon: '🌎', title: 'Cultural Competency', desc: 'Culturally responsive communication that honors the full context of patients\' lives.' },
        ].map(c => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 border border-mist shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">{c.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-deep-forest mb-2">{c.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-bark/70 leading-relaxed">{c.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ORGANIZATIONS -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-xs tracking-[4px] uppercase text-earth mb-4 font-body">Experience</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-deep-forest mb-4">
      13+ years. Trusted by leading <span class="italic">healthcare organizations.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="text-bark/70 leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Michelle has provided certified Spanish interpreting across major health systems and
      community nonprofits throughout the Bay Area — bringing the same standard of care
      to every organization, regardless of size.
    </p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
      {[
        { name: 'UCSF Health', type: 'Academic Medical Center', icon: '🏥' },
        { name: 'John Muir Health', type: 'Regional Health System', icon: '🏥' },
        { name: 'Kaiser Permanente', type: 'Integrated Health System', icon: '🏥' },
        { name: 'RotaCare Bay Area', type: 'Nonprofit Free Clinic', icon: '🌿' },
      ].map(org => (
        <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6 border border-mist text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-3">{org.icon}</div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-deep-forest text-base mb-1">{org.name}</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-earth tracking-wide">{org.type}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-bark/50 italic text-center">
      Plus additional community health centers, behavioral health programs, and nonprofits throughout the Bay Area.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- MISSION STATEMENT -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 text-center">
    <p class="text-xs tracking-[4px] uppercase text-earth mb-6 font-body">The Mi Voz Mission</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-deep-forest mb-6">
      Language should never stand between<br/>
      <span class="italic text-clay">a patient and their care.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="text-bark/70 leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl mx-auto">
      Every person deserves to walk out of a medical appointment feeling informed, respected,
      and heard — regardless of what language they speak. That belief is the foundation of
      everything Mi Voz does.
    </p>
    <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-clay text-white font-medium px-8 py-4 rounded-full hover:bg-earth transition-colors">
      Work With Michelle →
    </a>
  </section>

</Layout>
